<Author>KimAtlanta
<Content>Nice Place!!! I had a nice stay at this hotel. The pool grounds were beautiful. The room in the tower was eye-catching and very modern. The bed was VERY comfy! I was on the 8th floor with a partial ocean view. There was some noise from partiers in the corridors on the weekend but it was nothing intolerable. There were plenty of chairs available at the pool and beach. The concierge supervisor, Tania, was very sweet. She sent a special plate of chocolate dipped strawberries to my room for my wedding anniversary. We had a fantastic anniversary dinner at Koco, where we were treated like royalty. The food and atmosphere here were amazing. We also enjoyed the BBQ restaurant on the 10th floor. We traveled with our six year old and the hotel felt child-friendly enough. There were people of all ages here. The lobby dress code is not an issue if you are just passing through. You can get out to the street or out to the pool without being formally dressed. It's only if you choose to stay in the lobby or dine in the restaurants then you need to be dressed up. We went swimming in the pools at night and it was great. I got a few small bug bites at night by the pool but did not notice any bugs on the beach or in the rooms. The drinks at the pool were not THAT expensive. It was $10 for a daquiri, which is what I would pay at a bar in my home town. There were plenty of fast food and casual restaurants to walk to if you didn't want resort food. There was also pizza in hotel for about $15. Overall this was a nice vacation! Thank you, Tania! 
