<Author>RRSp0rt
<Content>Think again before you book this hotel My wife and I booked a quick weekend getaway in what we heard was THE hotel to stay at in Puerto Rico. Having been to Puerto Rico many times and never staying here we decided to give it a shot. I read the earlier reviews of service being terrible in Puerto Rico, but we have had pretty good experiences at our previous stays at the Caribe Hilton and the El Conquistador.We checked in on a Friday and had no complaints. Our room was beautiful!! The pool area was also great. Our experience started to change when we ordered room service. It took approximately two and a half hours to get our meal. This however was the lest of our problems. Saturday morning we went to Starbucks and attempted to charge the coffee to the room, however I was told that my credit limit was exceeded. So instead of waiting on the long line at the front desk to see what went wrong i paid cash. We went to the beach for the day and when we came back to our room our keys didn't work. We proceeded back down to the lobby only to be told that our room was locked intentionally. The clerk at the front desk gave an explanation of my credit card being refused. Being that I don't have a limit on my credit card I found it interesting and asked to have they keys back to the room so I could go to the safe and get my phone to call my bank. They would only let me go the room with a security guard. Once i called my bank they told my card was frozen for unusual activity. They read me the list of charges and everything seemed okay until they told me the charge at the El San Juan Hotel. The charge was double the amount of the quoted price of me stay. The clerk that put it through put it through nine times!!! Thats right nine times!!!The front desk denied it saying the only tried to charge $100 and it didn't go through. I am a loyal Starwood member and I will wait until the W is open in Puerto Rico until I return. 
