<Author>NewYorkDana
<Content>Not as Expected Was there with 6 friends for my 40th B-Day, We had a great time because that what we set out to do. After reading on tripadvisor about some of the awful rooms that were in the the garden lanai, we called the hotel to make sure we were in the renovated section. We were told that all rooms were renovated, not true. We were put in an area away from the main building that was filthy. Showers were dirty, dried urine on the toliet seat,mildew smell, gross. You needed a key to get into that section and out of 7 keys 1 worked. When we complained to the front desk we were told that they couldn't do anything about it right now but they would move us the next day to the best available room by 2pm. We waited until 5pm the next day and they gave us a room in the main buliding outside the elevator. My problem with this was that the hotel was empty and the front desk was not very accomodating, and almost annoyed by our request. Even the managers could care less. Even after not getting into our new rooms until after 5pm, we had to beg them to extend a late check out to us, keeping in mind that the hotel was not full. I felt that they just did not care. I'm not stretching the truth when I say the room was not clean. We packed up our stuff in the morning and left it with bell service, because none of us wanted to stay another minute in those rooms. With all that said we did meet some really nice staff. Frances at the front desk tried to be helpful. We meet a great waitress Yashenia at Uncle Bob's. I had a great massage by Millie at the spa, even though the spa did not have many amenities. A great meal at Koco's with great service. The beach was clean, but not enough chairs, and charging $10 for umbrellas a day is a bit much, especially because there small and you had to rent several for a group. Your on a tropical island, your going to need a umbrella at some point. the pool was very clean, but did not like the cushoned lounge chairs. Some were covered with terry cloth covers others were not and had mildew on them and stained with body oils. Will not be back, definitly not as I expected. To be honest traveled many places and never experienced such poor front desk service. Especially from managers. 
