<Author>jens3boys
<Content>Loved the El San Juan We stayed at the El San Juan for 3 nights post-cruise, Aug 10-13.We are a family of 5...mom 49, dad 56, 3 sons 16, 19, and 20. I got 2 rooms through Priceline for $115/night/room. I was very apprehensive about staying there after reading so many bad reviews on Trip Advisor. If you are staying here, rest assured that the hotel is wonderful! I emailed them as soon as I won my bid on Priceline requesting connecting rooms (1 king, 2 doubles) in the main tower with the renovated rooms. All of my requests were honored! We even had a partial ocean view which was lovely. We got to the hotel around 9 AM and of course the rooms weren't ready yet, which was to be expected. The front desk took all my info, including my cell # and called me as soon as rooms were available. The first one was ready at noon and the 2nd one around 2:00.We never had any problem with noise. The pool area is just beautiful. The hotel lobby is nice but too dark for my taste, but we didn't spend much time there anyway. We never had any problem getting extra bath towels as soon as we requested them. The renovated rooms are very bright and airy and I highly recommend asking for one of these rooms if you are going to stay here. I have no idea what all the bad reviews are about...we had no complaints whatsoever! If you book this hotel, you will not be sorry. I would stay here again in a heartbeat! 
