<Author>Sildex22
<Content>Great Stay Our hotel stay at the ESJ (as the call it) was great. The beach front is ideal and the service is excellent.But fair warning to all. When we first checked in we were told to head out of the main building (where the checking in takes place) and go through the pool area to the adjoining building where our room was located. Now, when you first get to ESJ, you are completely blown away by the lobby and the whole atmosphere being very chic and top class... ok, so we walk with our luggage throug the pool area to a building accross the way, and right away it's like you're in a completely different hotel. The little entrance and elevator we had to take were very very run down and outdated. We got to our floor and saw a long hallway and got to our room... well, let's just say that after seeing the lobby in the main building and then walking into our room I was royally disappointed. It looked like a dark, outdated style room. We decided, who cares, let's make the best of it, we'd be outside most of the time anyhow. But as I walked out into the balcony, I found lots of cigarette butts (even though we were supposed to have a non-smoking room) and used glasses and then we also realized we had gotten two double beds and not one queen bed!We called to complain and were told we had been given the wrong room and to please head back to the main lobby... we lugged our bags BACK through the pool area to the lobby and were told we were staying in the main tower. We went up to our room and WOW, it was like night and day, our room was UNBELIEVABLE, exactly like the pictures they have online, very mod-chic and super super clean. They even had an IHome alarm clock and LCD Screen TV. It was great!The service and attention were also great and the lobby area with 2 bars in the middle of it was great! We were there a saturday night and the lobby area (which is huge) turns into a party, with a live salsa band and the bars are flowing with people, there's also a casino right in the hotel.OH! and one last tip, do NOT use the tour company that's located in the hotel. You find/see their desk as you walk to the pool area. They share the desk with the Hertz rental company. They were AWFUL. It was the only regret we had of that trip. They were late picking us up for tours and we even missed parts of the attractions promised because of it. All in all It really was a great stay, but not sure if that is because we were lucky to have switched rooms.... 
