<Author>coupiehead
<Content>Can't wait to go back.... My daughter and I stayed at the El San Juan Hotel for 5 wonderful days in August. The weather was beautiful, the hotel was georgous and the staff was impeccable. We we totally pleased. I read all 320 reviews....after I booked our reservation.... lol.... and had some questions but any complaints I read were from people who have expectations that could not be met where ever they stayed. I communicated with Tania Sanchez over e-mail on many occassions asking qustions about tours, check in and she was more than accomodating. We arrived at approx. 1:30 and were greeted with a smile by a wonderful door man...his name is Hery. You couldn't help but to love this man, he was so kind and courtious. Anmando checked us in and was able to provide us with our room immediately even though check in is at 4:00 pm. We we thrilled with our room! It was sunny, clean, the bed was unbelievably confortable, the shower was just fine......for those complaints regarding the shower... just move the shower head and close the curtain!!!. The pools were beautiful and the hot tubs very enjoyable. Everybody, I mean everybody, including the attendants handing out the towels were superb! I would strongly suggest reading all the reviews and taking note of the many resturants in the immediate area. We had many wonderful meals and also enjoyed the fantastic entertainment in the lobby in the evening in the hotel. We did not have a car for 5 days and had no problem getting around. We found only 2 blocks away a bakery with yummy pastries and bagels, lunch menu, a supermarket in the same mini mall to buy soda and other items. We took the horse back riding tour and it was fantastic!!!! I mean fantastic! We also went to see the Rain Forest. Our only regret was being too busy and not just relaxing more on the beautiful beach. Becareful ......the time goes by real fast! What's better to wake up every morning with sunshine and people smiling. I can't say enough about the hotel, PR, and all the surrounding people. A real nice experience in PR! The luxery of the US and the beauty and pleasant, courtious people in PR, We loved it and are already planning to go back. Kim and Brielle in New Jersey 
