<Content>Great Staff We arrived around 1pm and had no issue checking in early. We were upgraded to a better category in the main hotel tower. The rooms are very trendy and have nice extras. But as other reviewers have commented, there is a reason why there were ear plugs in each room. We could hear our neighbors as if they were in the room with us. This might vary based on room or neighbors, as we asked other guests about their experiences and not all had issues. On our second day we spoke with the front desk and they were great. They moved us to a garden lanis room with a private patio and jacuzzi tub. These are the rooms that haven't been updated yet, but they were clean, quiet, and very romantic.Koco had great food - yes the prices might be high, but no higher than at any other resort or metropolitan city. We tried the Agave restaurant on the 10th floor, but were not impressed with the wait staff and our salads had bugs in them.I'm considering a destination wedding in Puerto Rico and went to check out the property as potential location. Event space is beautiful with many options to customize your event. The banquet manager (Cristina Ramos) is very responsive and had great suggestions.Both issues we commented on (the noise in the first room and the food) were quickly addressed by the management who were easy to work with and eager to please. 
