<Author>antnyp73
<Content>Great resort with just some minor hitches... I went to the El San Juan this past January because my friends were having a small wedding there. What I liked: The hotel is literally a 10 minute cab ride from the airport. PERFECT!The Room - VERY clean and modern with a safe and a flat screen TV and iPod radio. Also, I've read some of the negative reviews and have no idea where the BED BUG comments are coming from. The rooms are VERY clean - the hotel in general is.The Staff - Friendly and accomodating. Upon arrival, we were upgraded to a better room (big PLUS in my book)What I didn't like:The noise from the disco on weekends is unbearable. When you book, make sure to tell them that you want to be far from the disco. The bass THUMPS until 5am. If you're into that, fine. But if you're going for relaxation, make a note. I will say, the manager was very nice about my complaint - she switched my room and took that night off of my bill. Another big PLUS!What I LOVED!The pool area. 3 amazing pools, many hot tubs, great lounge beds by the ocean, beautiful landscaping (like tropical gardens) and the pool-side staff is wonderful. The Lobby: First of all it is HUGE. Many different bars/lounges throughout - something for everyone. At nite (especially on weekends), it is very chic, so make sure to wear your Sunday best (Men - blazers, dress shoes. Women - dresses, etc.). There is also a small casino. It's not Vegas, but it's very fun.The restaurants: There is a great selections of places to eat right in the hotel: The Palm (steakhouse), a very good Italian restaurant, Japanese hibachi place, a new Mediterranean cafe. There is also a casual pizza joint and a Starbucks.I am actually going back to the El San Juan in July. It is a very beautiful place and I definitely recommend. 
