<Author>beachgrl86
<Content>Great Hotel So, I've been reading the reviews about the ESJ since I booked my trip. I had visited the hotel many time before and have LOVED it, but this was my first time staying there. Now, I am the type of person that stays at nice hotels, but not 4stars. I think thats where the difference came. For me, everything was great. However I heard couples in the loby complaining that it was the worst hotel, and that they are used to being spoiled. That said, the hotel was amazing for me!We arrived at the hotel around 1PM and got right into the room. It looked just like the website. Clean, colorful, neat, gorgeous! I can understand the shower curtain issue in the bathroom but if you tuck the curtain it no water goes on the floor. PLenty of space in the room though. Bed was very comfortable as well. As far as the pool area goes. Yes, people do get up and reserve chairs very ealr. They usually clear out around 3PM. The whole outdoor area was very clean and well maintained. I personally enjoy the beach much more so that is where I spent all of my time. Chairs were always available all day long. Eating at the hotel, as in most hotels is pricey. The first day we got there we walked to the grocery store (major supermarket Pueblo) and bought beer and wine there, as well as some snacks and water, as well as a bucket. Every morning we would oack up our water and beer and fruit, fil up the bucket with ice from the ice machine and head down to the beach. Much cheaper than ordering drinks from the bar all day. I guess we are pretty low maintenance. At the hotel we ate at the Palm ( always good and you know what to expect), and Koco. Koco was amazing!!!! The place is gorgeous and the food is delicious. The short ribs appetizer were delicious. For dinner we had the halibut and tuna which were so delicious. You must try this restaurant if you go there. Very romantic as well. Overall, if you are looking for a nice hotel with a great atmosphere this place is perfect. The hotel and the grounds were fabulous and every experience we had with a worker was great. Can't wait to go back. 
