<Author>fungirlconnecticut
<Content>Others did not see what I did.... I was not looking forward to our trip to the EL San Juan because I read the reviews here on trip advisor. DON'T BELIEVE EVERYTHING YOU READ!!!! Our trip there was wonderful. The hotel and grounds were VERY clean and well maintained. The staff at the hotel couldn't have been nicer or more helpful. I did not encounter one difficult or unfriendly employee. I mean this. I am not making this up. When we arrived, our room was ready. (We arrived at 11:00am. ) We requested a TowerRoom and were in the room within 10 minutes. Unfortunately, I did not like the room because it was too futuristic and cold looking and it didn't have a balcony. This was the only real dislike I had and it was somewhat subjective on my part. I went downstairs and spoke to Yvonne Ramos. She is the assistant desk manager. I cannot say enough about this lovely woman. The El San Juan is very lucky to have some one at the front desk with her people skills. ( If you encounter ANY problems while you are there, ask for her!) When I expressed my disappointment with the lack of a balcony, she said she would give us another room in the garden lanai area. She also told me that these rooms were not really updatedso I should know that . However, if we would leave our cell phone number she would call us when someone checked out so that we could see if we liked that room better. She went on to say that she only wanted to make us happy with our stay at the hotel and anything she could do to help us, she would. Can't ask for more than that! We also were allowed to stay and use the room we were first assigned until another became available. We also went at a very busy time. April 18- 26. The lanai room was perfect for us even though it was older and we enjoyed hearing the couqui frogs at night. The casino and lobby areas were always busy and there always seemed to be something going on. (Live music, bars, some people dancing, HOT club, restaurants etc.) The beach was beautiful and again it was clean and well maintained. There are a limited number of umbrella's at $10/day so if you want to stay on the beach for the day and you need shade, you might want to get one. However, you can also get a chair under one of the plam trees and not have the umbrella. We were in love with the lounges by the pool with the billowy curtains on them. I will say that on a busy time, you need to get up at 6:45 am to get one. The towel hut opens at 7am and you have to be there to put your towels on them. This being said, Wes is the pool manager. He will find you chairs etc. even if there does not seem to be any. If you don't use your lounges and leave towels on them to reserve them, they will be taken offafter a half hour if the hotel is busy. I loved being up early as the staff is out cleaning at 6am and the hotel is so pretty in the morning. You can get your coffee at Starbuck's and walk the beach. A word about Starbuck's.. there are two. Go to the one in the Galeria(right around the corner from the one in the lobby). There is usually not a wait at this one.  You can walk right out the front door.. to the right there are Wendy's, Burger King and some local food places. Nice if you want something less formal ( and expensive) than the hotel. Also, right next door is the Inter-Continental. We played at their casino but I would NOT recommend this hotel over the El San Juan. It is older and smelled musty. Some of the slot machines in the casino still used coins!!! However, half of the hotel rooms do have the ocean view as they face the ocean. On the left side of the hotel is Lupi's a fun bar for a beer, nacho';s etc. Also, there is a Denny's ( we went there for breakfast one morning) and the Ritz. The Rtiz has a great casino that serves soup and sandwiches right on the casino floor! We had the best meal while we were in Puerto Rico at the Ritz at the Il Forno restaurant. (Italian) This meal was so delicious,the restaurant was very romantic and was the highlight of the food portion of our trip. Make reservations and eat there, you will not be disappointed. All in all, I think that the El San Juan has been given a very bad and undeserved poor review. Our experience was nothing but wonderful I will go back again and hopefully stay in the oceanfront lanais. ( the newest and most expensive!). Enjoy your trip and don't let bad reviews spoil the anticipation of your vacation. 
