<Content>Something's Not Right Here My wife and I needed a quick break, so we booked a 4 day weekend stay directly from the hotel web-site. It is such a huge plus that this resort is so close to the airport-you can get your bags and be on the beach in 15 minutes....but....We specifically reserved a 'Garden Lanai' room, because thats the kind of setting we prefer when we go to an island. But even tho we went down on the first flight in the morning out of Newark, and arrived at the front desk at 11:30 (long before check-in time) we were informed that all the Lanai rooms were booked, and we were getting an upgrade to the Tower. Now, if I wanted to stay in a casino tower, I would have rather driven to Atlantic City. And what was considered an 'upgrade' from the garden was quite funny- a very small room NEXT TO THE ELEVATOR (noise all night long) and the smallest bathroon that I have seen outside of a boat. When we expressed our dissatisfaction to the front desk, the only answer was that all the reservations are really on a 'best-efforts' basis, and at no point over the 4 days were we able to get into one of the garden rooms.Getting a place by the pool is as competitive as getting a seat on New Jersey Transit at rush hour. If you dont park something on chairs by the pool by 7am, you are out of luck. But there is a 'guard' who will move things out of the way to make room for tip-paying latecomers, even if the people who had been in the chairs happen to be having breakfast 50 feet away!!!Very very strange way of treating customers...... 
