<Content>Very Disappointed I stayed at the El San Juan Hotel 13 years ago and thought it was one of the best hotels in the world. It's unique design and look as a Havana Hotel was incredible. The rooms were the best part as they were the ultimate comfortable room in look and design with dark woods, dark colors that made you feel like you were in a very cozy warm room.I was so excited to be staying there last week and couldn't wait to experience the Havana get a way again. I was shocked when I got there. The new owners have ruined the hotels look! It is almost blasphemous what they did. Fortunately they did not remove or paint over the beautiful dark wood walls and ceiling in the lobby, but they changed the furniture to Miami art deco couches and chairs and they are so impractical, they are not close to being functional or comfortable. If that wasn't bad enough, I couldn't help but laugh at the design of the guest rooms. The deep rich carpet has been replaced with white slate type tile. The walls are white, the furniture is white and totally unfunctional with their deco art design. The room feels so cold and hollow I could never get comfortable. Shame on the new owners for ruining such as classic great hotel!The pool and beach area is very nice and the service throughout the hotel was very good as well. Someone staying at the hotel for the first time will probably not have a problem with the changes, but for those who have stayed there and loved the unique ambiance, you will be very disappointed. 
