<Content>BELIEVE all the horrible reviews!!! This hotel has horrible service (from the lobby to the pool area), paper-thin walls, cheap decor, non-existent staff, unhelpful staff (that you can find), an ant-farm of a pool area, stained fabric on pool chairs, and ridiculous resort fees added to your bill. If you have an ounce of respect for your hard-earned money, don't waste it as this dump. LXR resorts, who bought this hotel from Wyndam, have taken a beautiful lobby and completely tried to modernize it by throwing in some neon blue lights and zebra sofas to accent the mahogany wood??? For a five-star hotel, the staff at the pool are not friendly, not interested in providing any type of service, and also pretty much non-existent. The hotel will put you in rooms near the elevator that they KNOW are loud due to the paper-thin walls. If you are lucky enough to get one of these rooms, your entire vacation will be ruined when you get no sleep due to the sound of a freight cart moving up and down all night on the other side of your wall. When you ask the hotel to help you out, they give you a woe is them tirade about how they are booked to capacity, etc-.--so somehow the fact that they cannot accommodate you, even though their business is service, is somehow your problem. Even when you get a new room in a few days of non-stop hounding them to please help you, the walls are so thin, you still will manage to get no sleep. The food at the hotel-run restaurants is terrible and so ridiculously overpriced. Stick to The Palm where you will at least get good food and service. I have stayed at the Ritz before in San Juan and it is well worth the money. TRUST ME---DON'T STAY AT THIS HOTEL IF YOU WANT TO ENJOY YOURSELF AT THE POOL, SLEEP, RELAX AND IF YOU WANT HOTEL STAFF TO BE USEFUL AND HELPFUL!!! 
