<Author>fourseasontravler
<Content>Check out the reviews BEFORE you stay at the El San Juan Hotel! Poor Customer Service and BED BUGS!!!!!!My husband  I just returned from a 5 night stay at the El San Juan Hotel  Casino in Carolina, PR.Our Experience: Upon arrival, we found our room to be less than clean. The remote control to the TV was not working and the thermostat was broken. We complained to the front desk and they said they would take care of it. The next day they fixed the remote and the thermostat. The maid came and went and the room was no cleaner than when we arrived. I left her a tip mid-stay to encourage better service and the toilet paper roll which was empty in the bathroom was not even replaced and the bathroom/vanity area floor and tub was still dirty. Multiple trips to the front desk to get my room key to work was frustrating.You had to get up at 7 a.m. to reserve a lounge at the pool because the guests would go down and put towels on them and not return until several hours later or not at all. Some guests would just come and remove your things and put their own stuff down and when you returned, your chairs, towels and personal items were moved. The hotel did nothing to enforce a time limit on how long you could hold a lounge which created fights among customers and a stressful environment. After all, you go on vacation to relax. Who wants to worry about getting up at 7 a.m. so that you can get your place in the sun!The lounges against the beach were full of ants and there was an open sewer behind us and every time the wind blew in our direction, we almost gagged. We complained to the management and they tried to get the cover on the sewer but it didn鈥檛 fit so they threw towels over the open parts.The pool area bar and outside restaurant did not have enough servers. There was only one particular waiter that was great. When he wasn鈥檛 there, it was all down hill. We sat down to eat lunch and waited over 20 minutes and when no one came to take our order, we got up and moved to the bar to order. We waited another 15 minutes before the bartender even acknowledged us and then witnessed a fight between another customer and the bartender because the other customer had been standing there for 20 minutes just waiting to order a drink. The bartender told him if he didn鈥檛 like it, to go to another bar鈥e left in a huff. We finally got our lunch, but my $15 burger was cold and not at all good.Prices are very high considering the level of service and comfort. Our first breakfast cost us $65.00 (eggs, coffee and juice) and it was nothing exceptional. Wasn't looking for a bargain, just good food and service.We went to the Italian Restaurant (La Piccola Fontana) in the hotel lobby. Pretty place, nice ambiance, usually good food, good service. There was a fly in my husbands water. Ok, that happens. We brought it to the waiter鈥檚 attention and he removed the glass, apologized after he made a joke about not charging extra for the fly and brought my husband a new glass. I then found a crab barb embedded in one of my shrimp. When I brought this to the attention of the waiter, he apologized and said thank God I didn't choke on it. At the end of the meal, they brought us complimentary drinks. We were ok with the little mishaps and went into the lobby bar after dinner. About a half hour later, my husband said he felt sick and had to go to the room. We never left the room and he spent the whole night in the bathroom. We complained to the front desk manager the next morning and she said she knew the owner of the restaurant and that she would mention it to him and we would get a call. No call ever came, no follow-up to us was ever made by either the hotel or the restaurant owner (not sure if they even got the message).Perhaps the most disturbing concern is the bites that we got all over our bodies. I went to the doctor when I returned and he confirmed that it was bed bug bites. We have pictures but not sure if appropriate to post because of the locations of most of them. Our room # was 363. In addition to itching and applying cortisone to all my bites, I spent two whole nights after our return, washing EVERYTHING we brought with us whether or not we wore it and storing our suitcases outside in the cold just in case any of the critters decided to 鈥渉itchhike鈥?home with us. THIS was no vacation!We filled out the customer survey that was sent to my husband via email and no one has contacted us about it as yet.The hotel grounds itself are very pretty and it would be a wonderful place to stay if there weren't so many other serious issues to be dealt with. We would not return to this hotel, nor recommend it to others. They may have renovated the lobby and the rooms in the main building but they need to get a handle on customer service and attitude of their wait-staff and they need to INSPECT and CLEAN their rooms! No one should go home with Bed Bug BITES!!!!!! 
