<Author>ElSaxiDad
<Content>Do Not Go To This Place!!! There are some people writing reviews that say don't listen to the whiners, that there stay was great. Well they're wrong. This hotel may have been good once, but it stinks now.For starters, my wife and I were bit by bed bugs, all over our bodies. Terrible... We didn't believe it until we got home and a Doctor confirmed they were bed bug bites. We had to quarantine our luggage and ensure all our clothes were washed or dry cleaned before bringing them back into our house. We stayed in room 363 in the Garden...The room was absolutely filthy. There was hair on the floor of the bathroom. The rugs weren't vacuumed. Even after we called Housekeeping and they cleaned the room, it remained filthy. They never washed the floors of the bathroom. The toilet flush broke. I had to fix it myself. It smelled bad (the water), like a sewer smell. The remote control for the TV was broke. The radio they provided in the room didn't play well. They removed the balconies in the rooms to make the rooms slightly larger. That stunk. At the pool, it was a constant struggle between the guests, for space around the pool. With not enough lounge chairs for the guests, and poor management at the pool, the guests are left to their own devices, securing spots at the pool by arriving there at before 7 AM, placing towels and belongings on the lounge chairs and hoping some disgruntled guest doesn't remove your stuff while you're getting a drink or something to eat.Some of the help at the hotel are very very nice. Others, not so nice. But some are really really nasty. Well, you have to take the good with the bad, right? I don't think so. Again, poor management allows this kind of behavior to exist and there are no standards in force. We actually observed one bartender tell a guest (who had waited patiently to be recognized by the bartender for 10 minutes) to go to another bar if he didn't like it.We're sitting at the pool and we smell this really foul sewer smell. I do some checking and find a sewer cover off, right behin the chaise lounges where we're sitting. I had to complain 10 times and wait hours for someone to come and put the cover back on.We went to the restaurant there callled La Picola Fontana. First, I found a fly in my water as I attempted to drink it. Then, my wife found a large pointy piece of crab shell in her shrimp when she bit into it. She could have choked. The manager tried to do the right thing and brought us both drinks and coffee. That was truly nice. Then we left and about 1/2 hour later, I was stricken was food poisoning. I was up ALL night. Not a good thing. I brought the incident to the attention of the hotel manager, not the desk clerk or concierge. Nothing was done. No, I am sorry from the restaurant owner, nothing...I sent the hotel an email, describing all this above. They never answered me. I considered not sending this but you know, I need to let people know to avoid this place like the plague. If it's between this place at almost $400 a night for a room or the Ritz at $550 a night, stay at the Ritz. So you spend another $700 but at least you get to enjoy your vacation. How can my wife and I get that time back we lost., never mind the $$$. 
