<Author>Driver59Boston
<Content>Very Nice Stay at ESJ I just returned from 5 nights at the El San Juan with my 17 year-old daugther and an adult family friend. Perhaps because we had just flown in from Boston where the weather has been absolutely miserable, we were more than satisfied with the overall ambience, amenities and condition of the hotel.The ESJ is not perfect, but nothing we experienced would keep us from coming back. Pros and cons:PROS:- Beautiful grounds, pools and beach. On the week April 16th there were mostly families and older couples poolside, and no problems w/ rowdy college kids or bikini contests, etc. The beach was clean, and there was a strong security presence at night which felt good for late night strolls/swims.- Every staff person we encountered was gracious and welcoming. Cool towels and frozen mojito samples are delivered poolside! We had no trouble finding empty pool chairs and never saw one squabble over territory. We did arrive at the pool by 8:00 a.m. most days.- There are many dining options both in and outside the hotel. We had very nice meals. Yes, things are overpriced, but not outrageously so (except for my $17 Mimosa at the main bar, which hardly contained half a glass of champagne)- Unlike other reviewers, we found housekeeping to be quite efficient.CONS:- While the renovated rooms are clean, they are quirky, especially the shower. (The beds are EXTREMELY comfortable however) The walls are very thin as one person stated. Fortunately, we had quiet neighbors. I can see this being a problem if you weren't adjacent to considerate people. If you are very fussy about the decor and efficiency of your room, you probably won't be happy here. We really didn't care - we wanted to be outside.When I book again, I will make sure in advance that there are no promotional events taking place at the time of my stay. I'm sure I wouldn't have liked the blaring music, etc. Overall, it was a very relaxing, fun and enjoyable getaway. 
