<Content>Will Not Go Back I will not be returning to the El San Juan although I have stayed there several times in the past. First the pros:Gorgeous lobby and loads of night life; the bars are great fun and the pools are decent. The restaurants--especially the Palm and the Japanese restaurant are excellent (even thought the Japanese restaurant is not even listed in the dining section of the hotel literature kept in the guest rooms. The beds are very comfortable and the new decor in the guest rooms is light, airy and pleasant. The luncheon offered at the outside bars is good and the hamburgers are delicious. Now the cons:The hotel was teeming with college kids. In the middle of out stay, Coors Lite sponsored a poolside party replete with a bikini contest. Apparently this event occurs 3 times a year. You could not enjoy the pool at all that day and there were many complaints. House music blasted throughout the pool area and adults (those of us over 25) had to find somewhere to escape.The housekeeping stinks. The rooms are not cleaned thouroughly and the housekeepers forget things like wash cloths, shampoo, soap, and shower caps. There are no full length mirrors and the phone is on the dresser--so if you are in bed you cannot reach over and answer it. There is also no bathtub or make-up mirror. Moreover, the rooms are NOISY, NOISY!!! No soundproofing at all. We could hear our neighbors talking and their television as well. Finally, the hotel made the perplexing decision to remove ALL OF THE BALCONIES from the renovated rooms.Next time, I am in Puerto Rico--I will stay at the Ritz and visit thelobby at the El San Juan at night. I recommend you do the same.Knight Traveler 
