<Content>Overpriced...Stay Somewhere Else This hotel has a beautiful lobby. It advertises that it is a 4 star property. It is priced four star but the service is a 1 star. It is regularly around 300 plus per night. We paid 275 per night through hotwire. It was far from a deal, more like a steal with the hotel doing the taking. On top of the money paid to hotwire I had to pay a 14% resort tariff per night which came up to another 30 something dollars. The rooms are really nothing to brag about either they were not 4 star furnishings. No iron, no ironing board in the rooms, no trash can in the room, no turn down service, nothing to say Hey I'm a 4 star Hotel. I took a few drinks out of the in room refrigerator to put a bottled water in and was charged 23 dollars. I did not drink any thing but was charged, go figure. The lady at the check out was nice enough to remove the charge. The bathrooms are very small, the shower does not have a door that can be closed so water gets all over the floor. What a mess. What I disliked the most was the poor service. When I checked in the first night, I was placed in a small room with 2 queen beds and a view of the top of some part of the hotel. I asked for a room with a king bed and was told none were available. So I settled for it the first night. We were tired and went in for a shower the previous guest's hair was all over the bathroom floor. I called for housekeeping it took 4 more calls, a final call to the manager and 45 minutes to get a 300 dollar a night room cleaned. The next day I requested the king room and was moved in within 30 minutes. When I got in that room the air conditioner was broken and hair was on the sheets in the bed. I made another call concerning this and finally got the air fixed an hour later. Another day I needed an iron and ironing board it took 30 minutes to get it. The last day I called twice to get clean wash cloths by the time they came I had ran down the hall and grabbed some from a maid's cart and taken a 10 minute shower. This hotel is not big on service. They don't pride themselves in taking 4 star care of their customers. I will never come back again. Word to the Wise: stay somewhere reasonable and come enjoy the casino , the nice lobby and live entertainment. You will be glad you did. 
