<Author>im_on_vaca_again
<Content>Lots of hotels on this beach, choose another one!! My husband was to attend a conference at this hotel, so we decided to make it a business trip. The flight there was nice because we purchased an extra seat for the four hour flight. Walking into the lobby was quite impressive, but seemed a little out of place in the islands. It is however, perfect for NYC. Patricia gave us a room in the garden area. They were doing some planting, but the area was very nice, as were the pools. The beach was gross because of the large amount of seaweed scattered about. And hotel guests were expected to wear wristbands so security could keep an eye on guests versus the large amount of non-guests at the pools and beach.The problem was with the room itself. I've stayed at Best Westerns with visually more appealing decor. The walls were cracked and the paint peeling. The bathroom was in serious need of caulk, paint, tile, and new fixtures. The bottom line was the noise from the room directly below us.While sitting on the balcony on check-in day, I heard loud machinery (saws, drills, hammering, super strength vacuums) being used in the room below. My husband, who was sitting inside talking to patients on the phone, could not be heard over the din. I asked one of the workers what time in the morning they started work. I was assured they did not make noise until 10 am. Okay, fine. I don't like getting up that early on vacation, but I could go lay by the pool and get some sleep.At 8:35 am the following morning, my room was filled with the most obnoxious loud noises. Drills, industrial strength vacs, saws, hammers, you name it, it was happening ALL AT ONCE!!! I called the front desk, they sent me to security, they came out immediately and the noise stopped- - - for five minutes. My husband and I IMMEDIATELY went online to find another hotel and we packed our bags in less than 10 minutes. We ended up spending $20 more at the Caribe Hilton just 10 minutes from the airport and had the most wonderful time with their three tier pools, ocean overlook, beach, amenities, and nightly entertainment. If you want island fun and beautiful surroundings, do a lot of research before booking a hotel, especially one that costs what El San Juan does. You'll save yourself a great deal of stress on your vacation. 
