<Content>Needs a renovation of service We booked this vacation months ago, but found out the week before departing (from a disgruntled co-worker who had just returned) that the hotel was under major renovations -- with 2 of the 3 pools closed, and an abundance of noise. We contacted the hotel and asked for some form of reassurance/compensation and were told that we should have known about it and there was nothing to be done except cancel our trip and come back next year when the renovations are complete. Of course, they would not do anything to comp our airfare. So, frustrated, we decided to go and take a chance as it was a much needed vacation. We arrived to rooms not being ready but the hotel itself has grand lobbies and seems like it used to be the place to be. Once we got our rooms, we were discouraged to find them dirty (hair that didn't belong to us, cigarettes on our porch), and not of a class you would expect to pay $300+ for. Additionally, the spa was closed. I rechecked their website and none of this is mentioned. The service issues were consistent, with waiters at the outside restaurant who couldn't remember orders, us returning to our room in the evenings to find that housekeeping had never come, a less than clean pool (the only one that was open) and a basically unaccommodating staff. The only bright spot were the bartenders, who were capable and nice -- perhaps because they realized that we had money to spend and would type well for deserving service. All in all, you can see that this place used to be nice, and the grounds are under major renovations so they should be nice again. However, if they can't manage basic service and cleanliness when they are less than half full they would need to renovate their entire staff to get back up to the class where they deserve the rates they seek. For similar rates, I would go to the Intercontinental next store that has a much better attitude, and you can still visit the ESJ at night. Or, splurge a bit more for the Ritz down the road which is in a different stratosphere of class and service. 
