<Content>2 Night Pre Cruise Stay We stayed in one of the Casitas rooms before our cruise. We found our room large, furnished OK with a patio exit to the 2 pools next to the beach. I think the room price is based more on location with the colorful lobby and Galleria stores. The shower in the room was huge with two shower heads.The refrigerator was not working but not a big deal. We had a late check in and the non smoking room had been held for us. The staff was curteous, friendly, prompt and the room was cleaned very well. There is remodeling going on at other hotel areas but were were not disturbed by the activity. The lobby areas are very busy with night life especially on Saturday until late hours. If you want to try a very good, moderate priced restaruant that the locals enjoy, take a short walk out to the main street, turn right and when you see the Ponderosa Steak House on the left, enter the strip mall and look for a small restaruant on the left side. Very good Puerto Rico food and American choices as well. There is also a gift store next door with very reasonable prices. Try the Ponderosa for brunch on Sunday - very popular with locals. Just further down the street is a Walgreens. This as again a very short walk from the hotel.I would stay here again. 
