<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>What a Wonderful Vacation It is true that the rooms need to be refurbished-we stayed in the Garden Lanai in adjoining rooms. The rooms were spacious, with enough bureau and closet space. The rooms were clean and there was absolutely no signs of bugs in the interior. The room service was very accomodating, bringing up extra towels, coffee, etc. Our party consisted of 8, so this was a blessing. We loved sitting on the patio in the mornings and in the evenings. The beds were comfortable, and there were extra blankets in the large clost.The pools were wonderful, and the service to be was good 90% of the time. However, we have a suggestion for management- Don't close the bars and towel services so early. 5 or 5:30 is way to early when a person is at a beach and pool resort. i think 7 pm would be more in line- considering check-in is at 4 pm. Most incoming guests settle in their rooms, and hurry to this truly beautiful pool area and wham!!!! you can not get a towel nor a tropical drink to celebrate your 1st evening in paradise.The lobby and bar area were gorgeous! The bands were all very good. You can enjoy sitting there with your family and enjoy the evening. All the wait staff was extremely accomodating, and friendly. However...........When you reach the casino do not expect the same friendly service. If you play the slots you will need to bring your own drinks and your own ash trays. The waitresses only service the card tables and if you finally get one of their attention, they act annoyed that you ask them for a drink- be it coffee, water or alchohol. This was a big surprise to me, as I was there almost every evening. I finally got the hang of bringing in my own drink and ash tray from the bar. Management needs to take care of the gamblers, as i am sure they bring a good deal of revenue to this hotel. I think more care needs to be taken in this area, and your casino staff needs a lesson from your lobby staff.All in all a very enjoyable time, very good food in the restaurants, pricey but good. There are some smaller restaurants and fast food places out on the avenue that are worth checking out.A wonderful tropical experience! 
