<Content>It's Not That Bad! Positive Review! we're just back from xmas at the el san juan - stayed for 8 nights...our travel agent said that we should stay there because of the action in the lobby for the teenagers in our group of 11...after reading all the negative reviews on tripadvisor we were a little nervous and wanted to switch to the ritz carlton...but i can honestly report that it was a GREAT vacation...yes, the rooms are a little shoddy and we're used to staying at Four Seasons hotels...but compared to what i was expecting - it was totally ok...we had two adjoining standard rooms on the 7th floor...the staff couldn't be nicer - everyone has a smile and is helpful...we had no problem with housekeeping or checking in...yes, you can hear the planes but that's the price for a quick drive from the airport...the beach was beautiful and we had no problem getting 11 chairs set up for us every day...the guy at the beach, chicky, was amazing...the 2 pools are beautiful and the grounds are a tropical paradise...we lunched at the beachside restaurant = or just ordered at the bar and ate at our beach chairs...or we went to pizza place in lobby to bring back the most delicious pizzas and sandwiches...the coffee bar in the lobby was convenient for tea, coffee, and pastries.. the kids had lots of stuff to do on the beach = water sports were right there..there was a drugstore not to far away to stock up on snacks for the kids...the lobby at night was really something = tons of kids roaming around...the lobby is gorgeous, sort of like a las vegas hotel on a small scale except that it's the real thing = old world elegance...old san juan felt like europe - really fun to walk around...every restaurant was amazing...some of the best food we've ever had and we live right near NYC...i would put the food equal to food in las vegas and aspen...we ate at the palm in the hotel,kudeta in OSJ, fontana di roma (above hojo hotel), tangerine at water club, pikayo, pamela's on the beach, parrot club and al dente - both in OSJ...pikayo was delicious but the atmosphere was a little corporate and antiseptic and a little too fancy for the teens...that's the only restaurant i wouldn't go back to - and they charged $25 for a really tiny bowl of plain pasta that one of the kids ordered... so i give the vacation a TEN and would go back next year... 
