<Content>Beware of Moldy Mattress We stayed from Nov. 18 through Nov. 25, 2005. We made our Thanksgiving reservations the first week of April. I agree with most people describing the entry and lobby as beautiful. Unfortunately, we were unable to find a bellman when we arrived at 2:00 PM and proceeded to the front check in desk with our luggage. We were informed that check-in was at 4:00 PM, although it is still advertised on Wyndham鈥檚 web site as 3:00 PM check- in. By the way, we booked it because we are Wyndham By Request members only to find out that Wyndham sold the property. We came back at 4:00 PM and asked a front desk clerk for our room. He flippantly and rudely replied it wasn鈥檛 ready. When asked when it would be ready, he said, 鈥淚 don鈥檛 know, maybe around 5:00 PM.鈥?This was a Friday afternoon and the front desk area was virtually empty from the time we arrived until we got our room sometime after 5:00 PM. Any dealings with had with the front desk were well below satisfactory. (By the way, my sister arrived the same day at 11:00 AM and checked right in to the Intercontinental Hotel next door and got a beautiful ocean front room.) Although we paid for a 鈥渟uperior room鈥?which amounted to $320 for two of the nights, we were given a standard room that I can only describe as absolutely dismal. Our first room was on the 4th floor overlooking a well-worn roof. The patio and the furniture were absolutely filthy and the door only locked from the outside. We were eventually moved to a 鈥渟uperior room鈥?located on the 9th floor (931) directly above the original room (431). Although the view was better, the room was even worse. The patio was filthy, rugs stained and worn, moldy smelling, and bed covering appalling. In addition, all of the stereo equipment had been removed as well as the phone in the bathroom. The bathroom was extremely small and very well worn. We never saw the 鈥減lush鈥?robes that were advertised. If what I have already described is not enough for concern, we were abruptly awoken on the last night of our stay by water pouring down on us from the ceiling. We jumped out of bed soaking wet and looked at the ceiling tile gushing water and brown debris on the bed. We immediately called the front desk who sent two housekeeping people to our room. They took off the wet sheets, flipped over the soggy mattress and put fresh sheets on the bed. We asked where the water came from and they said the health club was on the floor above us. We never received any sort of apology from the hotel or even an offer of cleaning our wet clothes. If what I have told you isn鈥檛 enough to dissuade you from staying in this hotel, I advise you to beware of the beds you might be sleeping on, particularly in Room 931! 
