<Content>Beauty and the Beast I was in San Juan to celebrate my birthday and was very disappointed with this hotel. Upon arriving at the hotel and not being helped with my bags, I should have turned around and left then but I was happy to be away and thought no big deal. Let me start by saying that the entryway and lobby at first glance are breathtakingly beautiful. The employees are all rubbing and buffing the brass and polishing the old wood. You walk in and get an old world cuban feel. Then the lingering odor of stale cigars invade your nostrals. You approach the registration counter were in are given your key and directions to your room. (By the way if you were expecting a oceanview, don't. We were told the hotel was build perpendicular to the ocean so know one has a full ocean view except the $800.00 a day suites which are all ground level oceanview.)Once we walked a mile with bags in hand to the elevator that would lead us to our 2 flr room of the gardenview, panic set in because that's when all the beauty started to disappear. The carpets changed to a smelly moldy green floor pad. The carpet in front of my room 267 looked as if someone had spilled milky or soething white on it. I walked into the assigned room and could not believe what I saw in front of me. The ceiling tiles were wet and moldy. The dirt buildup on the sliding glass doors were so thick I thought it was tar. I could tell the carpet had not been vacuumed from the things I found on the floor and in back of the room chair. There was writting on the walls among other things on the walls. The vents had black sut masked across the entire opening. An once again the room smelled stale. I immediately called my agent who had me moved to another room until I could get out of that hotel the next day and into another hotel. The next room was in the Tower which I was assuming would be much better. Wrong again. I got to look at the roof of the building for my view. I had to clean the bathroom with cleaner I brought from the market across the street. There was rust in the tub and sink. There was no hot water. There was hair in the bed and it was not mine. Needless to say I was completely applauded. This place was a nightmare. I can't think of a better word to discribe it other than to say it was pure nasty. Just out and out dirty. I spoke with management who I must say was very receptive of my complaints and did make every attempt to correct what she could, but my mind was already made up to vacate this property. So much is spent on the lobby and it's upkeep that there probably isn't enough funds left to make the rooms nice. You go from Top of the line to bottom of the barrel in just an elevator ride. Not worth the money. Not worth half the money I spend. This should be rated closer to a 2* then a 4*.Motel 8 would have been better. What they need to understand is that the room is the first thing you see in the morning and the last thing you see at night. Vacationer should at the very least get a clean room. I ran into 6 other people who had at sometime or another stayed at this hotel with simular experiences. One couple stated that the hotel was being bought by a new company and that it would be updated soon. But they would not take a chance on returning. If dirt, mold and sut are part of your vacation requirements then this place is for you. 
