<Content>Great vacation, nice hotel, so so room... We just got back from staying in San Juan for a long weekend. It was a great time. 5 min from the San Juan airport. The hotel was nice. We stayed in a Casita near the pool. The room was a bit out dated and could stand to have a make over. My biggest complaint (if that is what your really want to call it) is that they need to add more lighting in the bathroom. There was this big beautiful shower that you had to step down into and it had 2 shower heads. Only problem was that it was kind of dark in there if you were showering after the sun went down. There is a skylight in the shower that lets light in during the day. Our room was clean and we had absolutely no problems. People were nice, pool was great. There were trees everywhere so there was no problem sitting in the shade if you didn't want to sit in the sun. Beach was beautiful and the resort provided chairs and there was a waiter/waitress serving you drinks on the beach and around the pool. Drinks were kind of pricey, but what do you expect from a resort??? We didn't eat at the hotel, but noticed that the prices for meals were expensive. We ate out side of the resort and had some wonderful food at reasonable prices. 2 nights we walked to dinner. Yes, there is a dress code for the lobby after a certain time, but we didn't find it to be a problem. We both wore jeans one night and no one said a word to us. A lot of people come to that hotel in the evening to go the club, casino or to hear the live band play in the bar area. It was really a good time.We went to Old San Juan and had a good time. Everyone was friendly, and you do not need to speak Spanish there. I did not meet 1 person who did not speak English. Some of the reviews mentioned that the town is kind of dirty. That is true, but I think if you can over look that you will be fine. Have you ever been to the streets of Newark? I think they are a lot dirtier.I wish we had more time there because there was so much more we wanted to see. We will definitely go back and I would recommend both the hotel and San Juan. Hopefully Wyndham will put some money into upgrading the rooms. 
