<Author>irvpost
<Content>A fair and honest review My wife and I travel extensively and are not what you would call top of the line travelers. We try to stay at places recommended here by people in our area. I have noticed that places New Yorkers find appalling, I find pretty nice, but on this occasion I will have to say they were right on the money.The hotel is a 2 hour drive from the Airport and it is an easy drive and I recommend it. Keep in mind that it appears red lights are optional when in rural areas. The Hotel. The grounds and facilities Are some of the most beautiful you will find and I compair them to the old Ritz on the Big Island. The elevators and the Trolly train to the lower villages are in excellent shape and work great. They are not as slow as some here have posted. The pool and Cabanas are very nice with all the lounge chaises having a 2 inch foam pad atop them which is very comfortable. The Resort is very large and is laid out nicely for strolling, however it is not very friendly to folks having difficulty with stairs. The rooms are very nice and comfortable with a mix of summer wicker and hardwood furniture that is up to date. The views are amaxing if not blocked by the numerous palm trees. We did not eat at the hotel so I will not comment on them other than to say they looked very elegant and others commented they food was excellent.The Service. We went in May and this is the end of the tourist season. BIG mistake. The week we were there they had opened the pool to all the locals and they did not hesitate to take advantage of it. The Hotel was 40% booked but the pool was 210% full. The day we checked in we were pleasantly suprised by the Friendlyness and hospitality. The bellman spent almost 40 minutes giving us the latest on everything from weather to best dinning. The Television wouldn't work and we went to call the front desk but the cordless phone in the room would not work. They said they would have it fixed in a few. We went to explore the grounds. We saaw a large sign that said no shorts or jeans in the common areas durring the evening. Wow. We asked at the desk and were told that all dinning was formal and that jeans adn shorts were not allowed in the main facilities after 6pm. That was it for eating at the resort. ( on vacation I'm a jeans and buttondown type ). Good thing we rented a car. That night the elevator stuck open at about 1 am. every five minutes the alarm would go off for 1 minute. We had to call the front desk but they had not fixed the phone. We then got a corded phone from the desk and it took a maintenance person 2 hours to fix the elevator. The next morning they began repairs on the common courtyard wherea fire had broken out in a birdnest built on a light. 6 am they began woking on it. This occured every morning and the work continued till about 10 pm some nights. The 3rd day the hotel began preparing for the Christion Dior fashion show. It was at this point it seemed that all guests became a nuisance. The hotel had placed a hold on our credit card for $300 per day. We went shopping and my wife went through the roof. She went to ask why so much was held and that is when The desk clerk threw a pen at my wife and Said I am not putting up with this ---- My wife can be a little demanding but she is not the type to get insulting ( she sorta kills them with kindness ). Over all. The hotel is Beautifull, the grounds imaculant and the little island is a charm. The problem was with the service. It may have been the season but there was definatly a sence that we were there to provide them with a job instead of they to provide service. This problem was limited to the front desk service only. I want to mention that everyone else at the Hotel was very nice and accomodating. 
