<Content>Wyndham El San Juan - a happy medium I just returned from a 5 night stay at the Wyndham El San Juan Hotel  Casino with my husband. I had read some of the negative reviews prior to leaving and was somewhat concerned but overall I had a good experience. Your experience will depend on your expectations and what you鈥檙e looking for in your vacation. I was looking for a nice hotel with emphasis on a good pool area a location convenient to area attractions. While I would be content sitting by the pool all day, everyday, my husband likes to have activities and things to do and see. We spent some time at the hotel pool and beach area but also spent a good part away and ate the majority of our meals off premises. I had no issue with our room. It was nice, clean, and had a very nice view. My biggest complaint is about the check in experience. I was disappointed in how long it took us to get to our room on arrival day. We arrived at the hotel at 1:00pm and our room was not ready until 4:00 pm, which is technically check-in time. However, I found the service at arrival to be terrible. When you walk in there鈥檚 no one directing you to the check in area. You walk in to a large lobby but there is no sign or person directing you the registration area. When checking in we were directed to the pool area but no information was given about the hotel or what to do for the 3 hours that we鈥檇 be waiting. We were able to fend for ourselves and actually walked outside of the hotel area and found a great little cheap restaurant across the street. I was disappointed that they didn鈥檛 direct us to a changing area (I found out about it when reading the hotel guide in the room) or any of the restaurants on site (lost business for them). The comments about service are probably accurate. It鈥檚 ok if you are fine w/self service, which for the most part we are, but if you really want a 4 or 5 star service experience you won鈥檛 find it here. The pool area is nice and spacious and you can be at the pool w/a view of the ocean. The pool/beach area is important criteria for me and I was happy here and the outside bar service was good. We spent only a little time on the beach after jet skiing. We took over some lounges and an umbrella and I was annoyed when I watched an employee talk to my husband and take the umbrella that other guests had left for us away. Once I got out of the water I found out that it鈥檚 $10 to have an umbrella on the beach, which I think is ridiculous given that I鈥檓 already a guest at the hotel but since we weren鈥檛 staying at the beach long I didn鈥檛 make it an issue. There is security around the pool and I did not find this to be an issue. I like that only guests are allowed in the pool area. I found outside pool area to be better and more spacious than that of the Ritz and could see people staying at other hotels looking to spend time at this pool instead. The lobby was nice but after reading about how great it was I didn鈥檛 find it that grand. We only spent a little time in the casino and it was also fine. We didn鈥檛 really participate in any of the lobby night life aside from walking thru or stopping at the casino. On the last night we found the rooftop bar/restaurants and spend some time at the Tequilla bar (on the 10th floor). This is worth the trip on the elevator and had a great view. The bar tender was great and we had great service and a fun night. We only had one meal at the hotel 鈥?breakfast at the Veranda. It was very good but I found it expensive. We were able to eat offsite for 录 of the price. A great place across the street is call Mi Casita and was great for breakfast or lunch. They had excellent coffee. A walk down the beach is the Blue Dolphin which is an interesting outside bar that you can walk to for a very casual atmosphere (walk towards the big restaurant sign). In Old San Juan we had dinner at Caf茅 Puerto Rico, which was also very good. There are plenty of restaurants around the hotel within walking distance if you don鈥檛 want to pay hotel prices. The tours offered by the hotel seemed very overpriced. We rented a car one day and went to the rain forest on our own. It was a great day of exploring. We arranged for the car through the concierge and it was very easy and convenient. For less than $50 (car rental + gas) we did the rain forest and beach tour plus our own exploration. With a tour it would have cost $132.00 for two of us. At the rain forest we did two short hikes 鈥?one up Mt Britton and one down to a waterfall where you could swim. It was fun and it wouldn鈥檛 have been included in the tour. We also went to Old San Juan a few times. One time we went via cab - $32 round trip + tip and the other times we took the bus for a $1.00 total roundtrip for two of us. The bus is fine. The stop is outside the hotel. It does take 30 minutes longer than the cab but it鈥檚 an experience in itself. Old San Juan is nice walking tour that you can do on your own. The forts are worth checking out and there are good restaurants. The weather was hot and humid. It did rain every day that we were there but usually only for an hour or so. We were there in May 21-26 and it was not crowded at all. Overall, Puerto Rico was pleasant and an interesting vacation. The hotel atmosphere was nice, the service was ok, some employees were great and others could improve, and the prices on the premises were high. Again depending on what you鈥檙e looking for this hotel might be the right fit. My husband would have preferred to stay in Old San Juan and I would prefer the Conquistador so Wyndham El San Juan was a happy medium for us. 
