<Content>Most Reviews Are On Target I didn't want to believe the negative reviews of this place since I was looking forward to our vacation in Puerto Rico. As stated by others, this is not a four- or five-star hotel. The rooms are dingy and old. (They are updating the rooms beginning August 2005). I did not mind so much b/c I don't tend to stay in the room all day. There were 2 tiny bugs in our bed and that freaked me out.The lobby is nice, but not as spectacular as some readers say. It is hopping on the weekends and a nice place for a drink during the week. Even though it is not as magnificent as I imagined, it is the best lobby of the other hotels I visited. The casino is so-so. The casinos at the Ritz and the Intercontinental were 10 times better. The dealers at those casinos were also nicer than the dealers at the El San Juan. The pool area was nice, but again, it was dirty. The lounge chairs were dirty, the pool was rarely skimmed out, and the bars at both pools were dirty. If you touch the wall in the pool, it feels slimy. The pools at the Ritz and the Intercontinental were just as nice, but cleaner. The concierge at the ESJ helped me book reservations for dinner. We booked Tequila Bar for a Tuesday night, only to find out that it's closed that day! I would've thought the concierge would know this!The restaurants we went to were great. I recommend the Palm (steak!), Piccola Fontana (excellent Italian) and Yamato (great, fresh sushi).All in all, I would not stay here again, but I was able to enjoy my vacation. 
