<Content>Not nice! Let me just say first that we did not stay at this hotel but visited it for dining while staying at the Ritz next door. I also visited it for dining and nightlife two evenings last Fall while staying at the Intercontinental. Even though I had read numerous negative reviews in the past I was considering staying for a future visit because I had enjoyed the nightlife there and found two of the restaurants to be very good (the Palm and Fontina Piccolo (sp?) which had excellent Italian food!), (don't visit the Mexican restaurant as we found the service to be horrendous and the food mediocre). I was curious to find out if pool area at the Wyndham was nice and thought if so maybe it would overcome the negative comments I have read about the state of the rooms. Upon inquiring if I could look at the pool area I was treated so rudely by the people at the front desk that I would never consider staying there. It is strange that you must use the restrooms out by the pool area but when I approached the pool for a closer look the security guard insisted I move away. It was only about 20 to 30 feet away but since there were no pool lights on and the area was poorly lit I couldn't really see it at all. This lighting situation seemed strange considering how concerned they were about security! I then explained at the front desk that I was considering a future stay and would like to see what the pool area looked like. Rather than offer to give me a quick view I was lectured about security. I have never encountered this type of rude unwelcoming behavior at any other hotel I have stayed at or visited. Most hotels are proud of their properties and would welcome future business and gladly show you around. I guess here they only really care about making a profit off the casino and bars and restaurants in the lobby area. Since a nice pool area is an important feature when I stay in Puerto Rico I would not consider staying here. I also found the security presence to be extremely heightened compared to the Intercontinental and Ritz that I would be concerned that the Wyndham does indeed have some sort of security problem there. Since the lobby and casino is heavily used by the general public I guess this would make sense. Although the security is oppressive they don't seem to be taking care of what is going on around the exterior area - we were practically run down by a car that accellerated upon seeing us crossing the street next to the hotel only to slam on the brakes at the last possible moment with the occupants laughing hysterically. This was upsetting enough but since I was crossing with my two children I found this to be extremely frightening. I just think the casino and lobby area attracts some unsavory characters which you can witness just by entering their parking lot. This didn't seem to be the case at the other two nearby properties. We also have stayed at the Marriott Stellaris Resort and Casino and found this to also have a safer feel around the immediate area. The bottom line is I would not recommend staying here. I have always loved Puerto Rico and have felt everyone to be so friendly and nice there in the past. The staff at this hotel soured me on that feeling. I definitely got the impression that their priorities were not set on their hotel guests but rather their business in the lobby. Do yourself a favor and enjoy the Ritz, the Intercontinental or the Marriott Stellaris. The staff at all three of these were so wonderful to deal with including the friendly and kind security. They also have great restaurants and lovely well lit pool areas. You can always visit the Wyndham for dining, nightlife or the casino if need be although personally I will make sure I go out of my way not to drop a dime there again! 
