<Content>Loved it! We stayed here in August 2004, and hardly ever left the grounds of the resort! The only thing I agree on with all the negative comments is that our room wasnt ready when we got there, and when we finally did get to our room, our Wyndham By Request member special gifts werent in the room (they were there the next day, around mid-afternoon) The lobby of the resort is beautiful - it has numerous bars (at least 4 that I can remember) and comfy chairs to sink into. It was also The Place at night - locals come out for the live music and dancing, and it was so much fun to watch. It's true that at night they have a dress code in the lobby due to the fact that it becomes a club of sorts, but we thought that added to the ambience. (After all, who really needs to see people walking around in bathing suits, flip flops and short-shorts at 8 pm in the evening when you're trying to sit down to a nice dinner?) Food was excellent, but not anything different from what you'd find in NYC. We asked the guy at the front desk to recommend a great local restaurant in town, and boy, did he hit it on the head! Ropa Viejo was AMAZING - we walked out of the restaurant wishing we were staying another night just to enjoy dinner one more time! The pools at this resort are really what made it for us... we lounged out all day long at the pool with the swim-up bar and waterfall.. there are also jacuzzis hidden all over the place (I saw at least 3). The casino was ok... If you are expecting something like AC or Vegas, you'll be disappointed - its much smaller than that - there's only a few tables - but they do have plenty of slot machines. (The casino at the Wyndham Old San Juan was a bit bigger) They also had Texas Hold-Em every night we were there, which my husband loved. All in all - I'd definitely go back. I do recommend it, especially if you can get a good deal online (we got 4 nights and airfare from NYC for about $649 a person) 
