<Content>Honeymoon Nightmare We were going to spend the first six nights of our honeymoon at the El San Juan before flying on to Nevis. The first night (July 14, 2003), we were robbed at gunpoint on the beach right outside the hotel. Apparently the beach is not safe, but they don't tell their guests this (we heard they warn their guests at the Ritz Carlton). They refuse to recognize that it is unsafe. When the manager asked if there was anything she could do, we asked her to help us find a way to leave as soon as possible. She said I'm sure you'll feel differently tomorrow, it's very safe here. The staff at the hotel is trained to repeat the phrase I'm sorry, but it didn't happen on our property. Also, while we were talking to security fifteen minutes after we were robbed, another couple walked past us to go out to the beach. We had to tell them what happened because the security guards made absolutely NO attempt to stop them. 
