<Content>Had a great time at ESJ. Just returned from a 5 day, GoGo tour, to San Juan. Stayed at the El San Juan and loved it. The staff couldn't have been friendlier or more helpful. The restaurants were very good, except for the western one, that was just OK. Loved the beach, the pool, all the bars and nightlife at the hotel. The salsa bands were super. The room was fine, just a small amount of condensation from the air. We hung out our Please make up room sign each morning and had no problem. We even had a turn down service each evening and a newspaper delivered to the door each morning. There was an international Police Assc. Convention being held the last few days, so it was pretty crowded. The planes didn't bother us at all. You would expect to hear some plane noise being just a mile or 2 from the airport. In all it was a very relaxing vacation. Loved the resort and the Puerto Rican people! 
