<Content>A great resort I stayed at the El San Juan with my girlfriend for four nights in early July. The hotel was excellent, and I really cannot understand the negative reviews. Perhaps it is just an expectations game.I got an excellent package rate on expedia.com, including the flight and the hotel. Check in was simple, the staff was without exception friendly and helpful, and the guests were very high class (Jets quarterback Vinny Testaverde was a guest). The hotel lobby was fabulous, and it was a great place to hang out in the evening. The pool was also great. The beach seemed nice, but it was very windy, so we tended to stay at the pool.I was prepared for the worst, but my room in the main tower was fine, and well above Holiday Inn quality. This is the Carribean, and the humidity is going to affect the rooms. There was some condensation dripping from the A/C vent in the ceiling, but that was no big deal. The bathroom was huge, and the furnishings were very nice.The hotel did seem relatively empty, and it is possible that service is not as good during a busy period.I would stay at the El San Juan again without hesitation. 
