<Content>Isla Verde....nice getaway We just returned from the El San Juan and we had a great time. Granted, it is not the nicest hotel I've ever been to, but it was worth the money. We got a great web rate on Wyndham.com. So, since the rooms weren't that $$$ I wasn't too concerned about the rooms being outdated. The casino was so fun and the restaurants were great. Yamato is better than Benihana here in NJ. The food there was outstanding. The beach is so-so. I grew up on the Gulf of Mexico so I'm a beach snob. It was just ok. The pool was great, swim up bar, lots of palm trees. Wonderful! The pool chairs are so comfy too. Well, all in all it was a great mini vacation. I'm not sure if we'll go back because we never go to the same place twice, but it was fun. Oh and yes there is a lot of airplane noise, but for the life of me I don't get why that bothers people. I hear planes all the time here in Philly. No big deal. Maybe the people complaining about the noise live out in the country or at least far from a metropolitan area and aren't used to city noise. who knows.... If you want complete peace and quiet go to the West side of PR. Isla Verde is loud and action packed. I've heard Ricon is awesome too. One more thing, try Maria's in Old San Juan, they serve enchiladas and tacos for lunch and make the best frozen drinks! It is located on Cristo Street I think. 
