<Content>Dreadful Experience at the el San Juan My wife and I called before we left JFK to say that we had read enough negative reviews about the Hotel that we wanted to make doubly sure we would not get a bad room for a week. We were told that we would be looked after. We were given room 731. The view of the empty beer cans and the roof were so moving! The aircraft noise? Woke me up from a dead sleep at 3.38am, 4.00am, 4.45am, etc. And if that wasn't bad enough, there seems to be a have at it policy for the guests, consisting of screaming, yelling, door slamming......all night long. Soft pillows? They don't exist. Wyndham By Request? Forget about it.Call security? Yeah, they really care. They have a restaurant there called the El Veranda. It is a breakfast buffet and luncheon place. The wait-staff is amazing. That is, you will not believe how any group of people could be this lazy. They want you to order from the buffet, give them a tip and leave. We ordered tomato juice and items off the menu--2 waiters in succession just walked away. And the rest rooms at this place? Off the main lobby the men's room reeks of urine. It is literally never, ever washed with a disinfectant. As for the El Veranda men's room, you need to wear Off!. It is also never, ever properly cleaned and the standing water breeds dozens of voracious insects. Save yourself the aggravation and go to the Ritz-Carlton next door or the Wyndham El Conquistador. The El San Juan is an expensive disaster. 
