<Content>Can't wait to return! My husband and I stayed at the El San Juan in June. The hotel was great. A true resort with live entertainment, excellent dining, hand-rolled cigars at the cigar bar [my husband loved that] and a classic casino.We booked the standard room without an ocean view in the main tower. The room was large but the bathroom was small and outdated. The view was less than spectacular [we had the city view]. But for the price, we were happy. When we return, we will pay the extra for the ocean view or the garden room.Also, this area of san juan is very close to the airport. You could hear the planes taking off from the room, as well as at the pool or beach.We also checked out the Ritz-Carlton [it's right next door]. If money is no object, that is the place to stay. But it was an older crowd along with some newleyweds. But, as it's in the same area, you could hear the planes from their pool area/beach also.Make sure you join the Wyndam rewards club, because they brought wonderful snacks and beverages shortly after we checked in. 
